 The police in Ekiti State, on Wednesday, confirmed the arrest of some suspected armed thugs. The hoodlums were said to have been nabbed at Ita Ore, Efon Alaaye, Efon Local Government Area of Ekiti State by military men on their way to Ekiti from Ibadan. The Police Public Relations Officer, Ekiti State Command, ASP Sunday Abutu, who confirmed the arrest, said that the suspects were being transported with five 18-passenger buses. He explained that they were driving along the Ijebu- Ijesa-Ita Ore Road when they were intercepted and arrested at about 3am, on  Wednesday, by soldiers. The PPRO said that the suspects were arrested with dangerous weapons such as locally made pistols, cudgels, and cutlasses. “They were arrested at a military checkpoint mounted at Ita-Ore in Efon, Tuesday evening. They were loaded with five 18-passenger buses coming from another state to Ekiti when the primaries of parties were about to hold. “The suspects are still with the military personnel and it is expected that they will be handed over to us soon,” he said. He assured that the command’s detectives would do a thorough investigation on the incident and prosecute those involved.